Where Excellence Thrives

At TELUS, we foster an inclusive workplace where Black professionals thrive. We offer flexible work, best-in-class benefits, scholarships, and initiatives celebrating Black achievements. Our dedication is evident in our scholarships, partnerships, and team member-led celebrations of Black achievements.

Embracing LGBTQ2+ diversity

At TELUS, we proudly support our LGBTQ2+ team members through inclusive benefits, gender-affirming care and our award-winning Spectrum Resource Group. Here, everyone can bring their authentic selves to work daily, fostering a genuine belonging culture.

Our commitment in action

We're proud of our progress in creating an inclusive workplace. Here's what our team members say about our culture:

93%

of my colleagues respect my thoughts and feelings.

94%

believe that TELUS respects team members with diverse backgrounds and identities.

89%

feel that TELUS values different ways of thinking and divergent points of view.
“As a biracial person of Japanese and Irish heritage, I have experienced the richness and beauty of multiple cultures. As a parent of a neurodiverse child, I have learned the importance of embracing every person's unique talents and abilities. I bring these perspectives to my role as Chief Diversity and Inclusion Officer. I believe celebrating our team members' diverse and intersecting identities will foster a culture where everyone feels connected and supported.”

Allyson McElwain (she/her)

Chief Diversity and Inclusion Officer

The TELUS team acknowledges that our work spans many Territories and Treaty areas and we are grateful for the traditional Knowledge Keepers and Elders who are with us today, those who have gone before us and the youth that inspire us. We recognize the land and the benefits it provides all of us, as an act of reconciliation, as recommended by the Truth and Reconciliation Commission’s (TRC) 94 Calls to Action and express gratitude to those whose territory we reside on, work on or are visiting. Learn more about TELUS’ commitment to Reconciliation.

Territorial Acknowledgement

The TELUS team acknowledges that our work spans many Territories and Treaty areas and we are grateful for the traditional Knowledge Keepers and Elders who are with us today, those who have gone before us and the youth that inspire us. We recognize the land and the benefits it provides all of us, as an act of reconciliation, as recommended by the Truth and Reconciliation Commission’s (TRC) 94 Calls to Action and express gratitude to those whose territory we reside on, work on or are visiting. Learn more about TELUS’ commitment to Reconciliation.
